<Link id="l00003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Part of the LLVM Project, under the Apache License v2.0 with LLVM Exceptions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="6"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="7"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="8"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The code below implements dead store elimination using MemorySSA. It uses</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the following general approach: given a MemoryDef, walk upwards to find</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// clobbering MemoryDefs that may be killed by the starting def. Then check</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// that there are no uses that may read the location of the original MemoryDef</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// in between both MemoryDefs. A bit more concretely:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For all MemoryDefs StartDef:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 1 Get the next dominating clobbering MemoryDef (MaybeDeadAccess) by walking</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    upwards.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 2 Check that there are no reads between MaybeDeadAccess and the StartDef by</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    checking all uses starting at MaybeDeadAccess and walking until we see</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    StartDef.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 3 For each found CurrentDef, check that:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   1 There are no barrier instructions between CurrentDef and StartDef (like</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//       throws or stores with ordering constraints).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   2 StartDef is executed whenever CurrentDef is executed.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   3 StartDef completely overwrites CurrentDef.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// 4 Erase CurrentDef from the function and MemorySSA.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1111"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;DeadBasePtr =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1112"><Highlight kind="normal">        <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a3ac5d9eb48038aa973017317279eadf5">GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset</a>(DeadPtr, DeadOff, <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/dsestate/#af22719f6b4218045e44871a8c6d82f4d">DL</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1113"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;KillingBasePtr =</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1114"><Highlight kind="normal">        <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a3ac5d9eb48038aa973017317279eadf5">GetPointerBaseWithConstantOffset</a>(KillingPtr, KillingOff, <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/dsestate/#af22719f6b4218045e44871a8c6d82f4d">DL</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1115"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1116"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If the base pointers still differ, we have two completely different</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1117"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// stores.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01118" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1118"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (DeadBasePtr != KillingBasePtr)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1119"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-deadstoreelimination-cpp-/#ac512d9d0a4bc8f26ff95ba31373e4173acebc97682d8036254b6ee04910656525">OW&#95;Unknown</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1120"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1121"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The killing access completely overlaps the dead store if and only if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1122"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// both start and end of the dead one is &quot;inside&quot; the killing one:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1123"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|--dead--|&lt;-&gt;|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1124"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |-----killing------|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1125"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Accesses may overlap if and only if start of one of them is &quot;inside&quot;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1126"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// another one:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1127"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|--dead--|&lt;--------&gt;|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1128"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |-------killing--------|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1129"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//           OR</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1130"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |-------dead-------|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1131"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    |&lt;-&gt;|---killing---|&lt;-----&gt;|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1132"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1133"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We have to be careful here as &#42;Off is signed while &#42;.Size is unsigned.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1134"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1135"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Check if the dead access starts &quot;not before&quot; the killing one.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1136"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (DeadOff &gt;= KillingOff) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1137"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If the dead access ends &quot;not after&quot; the killing access then the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1138"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// dead one is completely overwritten by the killing one.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1139"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (uint64&#95;t(DeadOff - KillingOff) + DeadSize &lt;= KillingSize)</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1141"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If start of the dead access is &quot;before&quot; end of the killing access</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1142"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// then accesses overlap.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1143"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ((uint64&#95;t)(DeadOff - KillingOff) &lt; KillingSize)</Highlight></CodeLine>
